<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: In 2011 Ronnie Cahana suffered a severe stroke that left him with locked-in syndrome: completely paralyzed except for his eyes. While this might shatter a normal person’s mental state, Cahana found peace in “dimming down the external chatter,” and “fell in love with life and body anew.” In a somber, emotional talk, his daughter Kitra shares how she documented her father&#39;s spiritual experience, as he helped guide others even in a state of seeming helplessness." name="description" />
